---
import SlideLayout from "@/layouts/SlideLayout.astro";
import "@/styles/reveal-theme-fmonper.css";
---

<SlideLayout title="Demo Presentation">
  <section>
    <h1>reveal.js</h1>
    <h3>The HTML Presentation Framework</h3>
    <p>
      <small>Powered by <a href="https://revealjs.com">reveal.js</a></small>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Slides</h2>
    <p>
      Not a coder? Not a problem. There's a fully-featured visual editor for
      authoring these, try it out at <a href="https://slides.com">slides.com</a
      >.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <section>
      <h2>Vertical Slides</h2>
      <p>Slides can be nested inside of each other.</p>
      <p>Use the <em>Space</em> key to navigate through all slides.</p>
      <br />
      <a href="#/2/1" class="navigate-down">⬇</a>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Basement Level 1</h2>
      <p>
        Nested slides are useful for adding additional detail underneath a high
        level horizontal slide.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <h2>Basement Level 2</h2>
      <p>That's it, time to go back up.</p>
      <br />
      <a href="#/2">⬆</a>
    </section>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Fragments</h2>
    <p>Hit the next arrow...</p>
    <p class="fragment">... to step through ...</p>
    <p class="fragment">... a fragmented slide.</p>
  </section>

  <section data-markdown>
    <script type="text/template">
      ## Markdown Support

      Write content using inline or external Markdown.

      ```python
      def greet(name):
          return f"Hello, {name}!"
      ```

      Instructions and more info available in the [docs](https://revealjs.com/markdown/).
    </script>
  </section>

  <section
    data-background-gradient="linear-gradient(to bottom, #283b95, #17b2c3)"
  >
    <h2>Custom Backgrounds</h2>
    <p>
      Slides can have different backgrounds — colors, gradients, images, or
      videos.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section data-transition="slide" data-background="#4d7e65">
    <h2>Transition Styles</h2>
    <p>
      You can select from different transitions, like: <br />
      <a href="?transition=none#/6">None</a> -
      <a href="?transition=fade#/6">Fade</a> -
      <a href="?transition=slide#/6">Slide</a> -
      <a href="?transition=convex#/6">Convex</a> -
      <a href="?transition=concave#/6">Concave</a> -
      <a href="?transition=zoom#/6">Zoom</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Speaker Notes</h2>
    <p>Press <strong>S</strong> to open the speaker view.</p>
    <aside class="notes">
      These are speaker notes. They are only visible in the speaker view.
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>That's all!</h2>
    <p>
      Check out the <a href="https://revealjs.com">full docs</a> for more
      features.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="/">← Back to site</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</SlideLayout>
